    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Unfortunately, it appears to be `by design` based on this code https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell/blob/master/src/Microsoft.PowerShell.ConsoleHost/host/msh/CommandLineParameterParser.cs#L1352-L1383.  It's doing a simple parameter binding which is a subset of the actual PS parameter binder.\r\n\r\nI'd be worried what scenarios would break if we try to change this.\n\n<blockquote><img src=\"https://repository-images.githubusercontent.com/49609581/aad0ad80-cdec-11ea-8248-a37bc0571bfd\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div><img src=\"https://github.githubassets.com/favicons/favicon.svg\" height=\"14\"> GitHub</div><div><strong><a href=\"https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell\">PowerShell/CommandLineParameterParser.cs at master · PowerShell/PowerShell</a></strong></div><div>PowerShell for every system! Contribute to PowerShell/PowerShell development by creating an account on GitHub.</div></blockquote>",
